===Etymology===
Absalom or Avshalom (אַבְשָׁלוֹם "Father/Leader of/is peace", Standard Hebrew Avšalom, Tiberian Hebrew ʾAḇšālôm). 

===Proper noun===
'''Absalom'''
# The third [[son]] of [[David]], king of [[Israel]]

====Translations====
*Dutch: Absalom, Absalon
*English: Absalom
*Hebrew: אַבְשָׁלוֹם (Avshalom)
*Italian: Absalone
*Swedish: Absalon, Axel

